              "displayName": "Karthik Kambatla",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
            },
            "body": "Is this similar to {{assignMultiple}} in {{FairScheduler}}?",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=kasha",
              "name": "kasha",
              "key": "kasha",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Karthik Kambatla",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
            },
            "created": "2015-08-17T01:30:11.210+0000",
            "updated": "2015-08-17T01:30:11.210+0000"
          },
          {
            "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12856480/comment/14698925",
            "id": "14698925",
            "author": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=srikanthkandula",
              "name": "srikanthkandula",
              "key": "srikanthkandula",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Srikanth Kandula",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "Etc/UTC"
            },
            "body": "Will look. Possibly. However, this arch allows any bundling policy. We will push through a couple different bundled policies. I suspect the packer+dependencies+bounded unfairness bundled will be novel.",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=srikanthkandula",
              "name": "srikanthkandula",
              "key": "srikanthkandula",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Srikanth Kandula",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "Etc/UTC"
            },
            "created": "2015-08-17T01:56:55.835+0000",
            "updated": "2015-08-17T01:56:55.835+0000"
          },
          {
            "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12856480/comment/14717267",
            "id": "14717267",
            "author": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=srikanthkandula",
              "name": "srikanthkandula",
              "key": "srikanthkandula",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Srikanth Kandula",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "Etc/UTC"
            },
            "body": "I looked. Sort of similar but not really. The similarity is that both allow multiple containers to be allocated within fewer calls. \n\nThe difference is in the policies and the complexity. Bundling allows any arbitrary subset of 'legit' tasks to be assigned. Whereas assignMultiple simply assigns the first few. For example, bundling can decide that the 2nd, 3rd and 10th tasks are a good choice in contrast to assigning just the 1st task (the others may not fit). assignMultiple does not allow for this.\n\nBundling is slightly more complex because the actual assignment is deferred till the loop finishes. Whereas assignMultiple assigns each task in place and keeps going.\n\nPatch is with [~chris.douglas] for an internal review.\n\nWe are pushing out a bundler that mimics the current scheduler. All the tests pass and there is no performance change. As expected. Note however that the allocations are still deferred.\n\nBetter bundlers are in the works.",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=srikanthkandula",
              "name": "srikanthkandula",
              "key": "srikanthkandula",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Srikanth Kandula",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "Etc/UTC"
            },
            "created": "2015-08-27T18:44:09.480+0000",
            "updated": "2015-08-27T18:44:09.480+0000"
          }
